

                  1.6 USES OF SHELL SCRIPT ?
 
  > Combines lengthy and repetitve sequences of commands into a single, simple command.
  > Generalize a sequence of operations on set of data, into a procedure that can be applied to any
    similar set of data.
  > Create new commands using combinations of utilities in ways the original authors never thought of.
  > Simple shell scripts might be written as shell aliases,but the scripr can be made available to all users and all processes.
    Shell aliases apply only to the current Shell.
  > Create customized datasets on the fly, and call applications.






